2c:["$","p","12",{"className":"text-ink-200 text-lg leading-relaxed mt-6","children":"Clients ask whether tightening the banner will hurt opt-in rates. In our data across 14 UK B2B sites, moving from a dark-pattern banner to a compliant one drops opt-in rates by 6–11 percentage points. That sounds bad. But Consent Mode v2 modelling recovers 70–85% of the lost conversions in reporting, and the conversions you do measure are higher quality. Net impact on pipeline: roughly flat. Net impact on regulatory risk: dramatically lower."}]
2d:["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"id":"faq","className":"font-display font-semibold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-ink-50 scroll-mt-24","children":"Frequently asked questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-6 divide-y divide-ink-700 border-y border-ink-700","children":[["$","details","0",{"className":"group py-5","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 list-none","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-ink-50","children":"Does the ICO actually enforce cookie guidance?"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"className":"grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full border border-ink-700 text-ink-300 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45","children":["$","svg",null,{"width":"12","height":"12","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"2.5","strokeLinecap":"round","children":[["$","path",null,{"d":"M12 5v14"}],["$","path",null,{"d":"M5 12h14"}]]}]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed","children":"Yes — the ICO ran a targeted enforcement sweep through 2025 on the UK's top 200 websites and continues to issue formal warnings and reprimands. As of January 2026, fines are aligned with EU GDPR maximums (up to 4% of global turnover). Real-world enforcement still skews to warnings first, but the ceiling is now meaningful."}]]}],["$","details","1",{"className":"group py-5","children":[["$","summary",null,{"className":"flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between gap-4 list-none","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-semibold text-ink-50","children":"Do I need a cookie banner if I only use analytics?"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"className":"grid h-7 w-7 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-full border border-ink-700 text-ink-300 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45","children":["$","svg",null,{"width":"12","height":"12","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":"2.5","strokeLinecap":"round","children":[["$","path",null,{"d":"M12 5v14"}],["$","path",null,{"d":"M5 12h14"}]]}]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-ink-300 leading-relaxed","children":"If analytics involves any non-essential cookie or any cross-site identifier (GA4 included), yes — the ICO treats analytics cookies as non-essential under PECR and they require prior consent. The narrow exception is strictly first-party, anonymous, server-side analytics with no client-side identifier."}]]}]]}]]}]
